    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26c.51-52_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">51</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        North St. Paul 9
                        Minn.
                        Nov. 10, 1958
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Thank you for your letter. I was happy to receive it. Also thank you for the clipping about your lectures 'A Cycle of the West.' We do not get them here in the Twin Cities area. If you have any available material about your lectures, I would be pleased to receive it.</p>
                
                <p>I hope this finds you well. And yes, I also did enjoy the fine group spirit at Oak Haven. I wish I could be a successful writer., that is, have something published. And even the money is handy when one is hungry or cold. <del/><add>W</add>e would be if we had none of it. I know for there was much lacking when I was a child. I have much to be thankful for, and I am.</p>
                
                <p>I know that your time and efforts are much sought-after; I do appreciate your writing to me. It has been very encouraging and I do so need it. Please tell me: does a writer need an agent?</p>
                
                <p>I am still plugging away at my writing though it is slow. I rewrote my short-short "Fisherman's Rut" and an agent in <hi rend="caps">N.J.</hi> has it. His name is Robert Oberfirst, Ocean City, New Jersey. He wrote to me and said that he was pleased with it, and was looking forward to an editor's reaction. He wants me to send him $20.00 as a placement fee for 1 year, and he wants 10% commission on sales. Please tell me &#8212; how does this
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26c.51-52_0002"/>
                    
                    sound to you? You see, I know nothing about terms expected. I haven't answered him yet.</p>
                
                <p>Will be waiting to hear from you. I am so thankful to have you for a friend.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Very sincerely yours,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Marvel Goetschel</signed>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>333 5th Ave. <hi rend="caps">N.E.</hi></addrLine>
                        <addrLine>No. St Paul 9</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Minn.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript>
                    <opener><hi rend="caps">P.S.</hi></opener>
                    <p>If you ever happen to be in the Twin Cities' area &#8212; my phone number is <hi rend="caps">SP</hi>ring 7-4951 would be pleased to see you or hear from you.</p>
                </postscript>
                
                <note type="curatorial"><hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT CENTER</hi></note>
                
